msContents.summary: Commentary on Maḥmūd ibn Muḥammad al-Jighmīnī's Mulakhkhaṣ fī al-hayʼah (Epitome of astronomy or Quintessence of astronomy), with a few marginal notes.

msItem.title: Sharḥ mulakhkhaṣ fī al-hayʼah
msItem.author: Qāḍīʹzādah, Mūsá ibn Muḥammad, d. ca. 1436

supportDesc.extent: 90 leaves : 235 x 160 (165 x 95) mm. bound to 238 x 172 mm
supportDesc.foliation: Paper, ii + 90 + ii; [1-94], modern foliation in pencil, upper left recto, including flyleaves.

scriptDesc.scriptNote: Written in riq'a script by Mirhassmad ʻAbd (Bouwman).

decoDesc.decoNote: 23 simple diagrams in red, red and blue, or red and black (f. 15r, 18v, 22v, 25v, 39r, 43r, 43v, 45r, 46r, 46v, 47v, 48r, 50v, 63r-64r, 70r, 77r-77v, 80r-80v, 83v, 85v); overlining in red and black; selected words and phrases in red.

binding.p: Modern leather with inset stamped medallions, possibly from an older binding.

origin.p: Written in the northeastern Timurid empire, now Central Asia, in the 15th century or 16th century (Bouwman).

history.provenance: Sold by Bouwman Oriental Books (Groenekan, Netherlands) to Lawrence J. Schoenberg, 28 Mar. 2005.
Deposit by Lawrence J. Schoenberg and Barbara Brizdle, 2011.
